rComments: Very interesting class. Engaging readings. I would recommend this course and professor to all interested in critical perspectives.

Always takes the time to talk with students. Classes are based on assigned readings - if you don't do the readings the class will be very boring. But if you do, it is often a very interesting class. Opens the floor for discussion, but many students in this class did not participate and obviously did not do the readings.

A fairly easy grader, could take him for an easy A, but it is not worth sitting through his lectures. A terribly boring professor who regards attendance as mandatory, despite not needing to go to the lectures for anything. There is no final and the midterm is based on the readings. Would not take again.
